The paper discusses modifications to the C4.5 algorithm for decision tree induction, specifically addressing the weakness of handling continuous attributes. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), computational intelligence (cs.NE), and statistical learning (cs.SI).
